      {
        "id": "philosophy",
        "title": "1. The Laravel Philosophy",
        "slides": [
          {
            "type": "topic-title",
            "title": "1. Philosophy",
            "subtitle": "Developer Happiness (DX) is at the core of every design decision."
          },
          {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "What is Laravel?",
            "box": {
              "list": [
                {
                  "emoji": "🎨",
                  "text": "<strong>Expressive:</strong> Code that reads like prose."
                },
                {
                  "emoji": "🛠️",
                  "text": "<strong>Opinionated:</strong> Provides a sensible, powerful default for everything."
                },
                {
                  "emoji": "🚀",
                  "text": "<strong>Fast-paced:</strong> Rapid prototyping to production-ready in record time."
                }
              ],
              "title": "A web application framework with expressive, elegant syntax. It takes the pain out of development by easing common tasks."
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "The Artisan CLI",
            "box": {
              "code": "# shell: php artisan list\n# shell: php artisan make:controller UserController\n# shell: php artisan migrate",
              "title": "Laravel's powerful command-line interface based on Symfony Console."
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "The Ecosystem",
            "box": {
              "list": [
                {
                  "emoji": "📦",
                  "text": "<strong>Composer:</strong> Dependency management for PHP."
                },
                {
                  "emoji": "🔧",
                  "text": "<strong>Forge/Vapor:</strong> Painless server and serverless deployment."
                },
                {
                  "emoji": "🛡️",
                  "text": "<strong>Sanctum/Passport:</strong> Robust authentication solutions."
                }
              ],
              "title": "Laravel isn't just a framework; it's a massive, cohesive ecosystem."
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "architecture",
        "title": "2. Core Architecture",
        "slides": [
          {
            "type": "topic-title",
            "title": "2. Architecture",
            "subtitle": "The Service Container is the heart of Laravel."
          },
          {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "The Service Container",
            "box": {
              "code": "$this->app->bind('HelpSpot\\API', function ($app) {\n    return new HelpSpot\\API($app->make('HttpClient'));\n});",
              "title": "A powerful tool for managing class dependencies and performing dependency injection."
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "Service Providers",
            "box": {
              "list": [
                {
                  "emoji": "🏗️",
                  "text": "<strong>Register:</strong> Bind things into the service container."
                },
                {
                  "emoji": "🚦",
                  "text": "<strong>Boot:</strong> Kick off logic once all services are registered."
                }
              ],
              "title": "The central place to configure and bootstrap all Laravel applications."
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "The Facade Pattern",
            "box": {
              "code": "use Illuminate\\Support\\Facades\\Cache;\n\n$value = Cache::get('key');",
              "title": "Facades provide a 'static' interface to classes that are available in the application's service container."
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "eloquent-orm",
        "title": "3. Eloquent ORM",
        "slides": [
          {
            "type": "topic-title",
            "title": "3. Eloquent ORM",
            "subtitle": "The most expressive ORM in the PHP ecosystem."
          },
          {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "Active Record Implementation",
            "box": {
              "code": "$user = User::where('email', 'alice@example.com')->first();\n$user->name = 'Alice Smith';\n$user->save();",
              "title": "Eloquent's Active Record implementation makes interacting with your database intuitive."
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "Expressive Relationships",
            "box": {
              "code": "class Post extends Model {\n    public function comments() {\n        return $this->hasMany(Comment::class);\n    }\n}\n\n$comments = Post::find(1)->comments;",
              "title": "Define relationships using simple method calls."
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "Eloquent Collections",
            "box": {
              "code": "$users = User::all();\n$names = $users->reject(fn($user) => $user->active)\n               ->map(fn($user) => $user->name);",
              "title": "Every multi-result set returned by Eloquent is a Collection instance, providing dozens of helper methods."
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "routing-controllers",
        "title": "4. Routing & Controllers",
        "slides": [
          {
            "type": "topic-title",
            "title": "4. Routing",
            "subtitle": "Defining the entry points to your application."
          },
          {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "Expressive Routing",
            "box": {
              "code": "Route::get('/user/{id}', [UserController::class, 'show']);\n\nRoute::middleware(['auth'])->group(function () {\n    Route::get('/profile', [ProfileController::class, 'edit']);\n});",
              "title": "Routes are defined in the <code>routes/web.php</code> or <code>routes/api.php</code> files."
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "Dependency Injection in Controllers",
            "box": {
              "code": "public function store(Request $request, UserRepository $users) {\n    $users->create($request->all());\n    return redirect('/home');\n}",
              "title": "Laravel automatically injects dependencies into your controller methods."
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "Resource Controllers",
            "box": {
              "code": "# shell: php artisan make:controller PhotoController --resource\n\nRoute::resource('photos', PhotoController::class);",
              "title": "Quickly create controllers that handle all CRUD operations."
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "security-auth",
        "title": "5. Security & Authentication",
        "slides": [
          {
            "type": "topic-title",
            "title": "5. Security",
            "subtitle": "Granular permissions and robust authentication."
          },
          {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "Authentication Guards",
            "box": {
              "code": "Auth::guard('api')->user();",
              "title": "Laravel supports multiple authentication 'guards', allowing you to authenticate against different user tables or token systems."
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "Gates & Policies",
            "box": {
              "code": "Gate::define('update-post', function (User $user, Post $post) {\n    return $user->id === $post->user_id;\n});\n\n$this->authorize('update', $post);",
              "title": "Authorization logic simplified. Use Gates for simple checks and Policies for model-specific logic."
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "Laravel Sanctum",
            "box": {
              "code": "$user->createToken('token-name')->plainTextToken;",
              "title": "A featherweight authentication system for SPAs and simple APIs using mobile tokens or session cookies."
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
